Begin SW_EndarEscapePodScr

short doOnce
short doAlso
float timer

if ( doAlso == 0 )
if ( OnActivate == 1 )
set doAlso to 1
endif
endif


if ( doAlso == 1 )

if ( doOnce == 0 )
FadeOut 2.0
DisablePlayerControls
set doOnce to 1
endif

set timer to ( timer + GetSecondsPassed )
if ( timer > 2 )
PlaySound "SW_Shipblastoff"
player->PositionCell 935 12448 13752 180 "Taris, Ruined Plaza: Medical Bay"
player->additem sw_BlasterRifleOld 1
player->additem sw_blastbolt 75
player->additem sw_vibrodaggertaris 1
player->additem sw_medkit 5
player->additem gold_001 750
player->addspell tsi_survguilt
Messagebox "On the way to the local cantina, you are caught in the early stages of the bombardment of Taris. Scrambling to find safety, you make your way into a local hab block, and on the way you grab a dead guard's gear in a desperate attempt to defend yourself. After what seems like forever, the bombs go quiet. Your home is gone. Venture out into the remnants and find a way off the planet." "Ok"
set doAlso to 2
endif

endif

End

Begin tsiAutoDoorJediValley

short doorRaised
short doorDistance
short doOnce
short raiseDoor
short lowerDoor

float basePos
float minPos
float maxPos

If ( doOnce == 0 )
	set doorDistance to 250
	set basePos to ( getpos z )
	set minPos to ( getpos y - doorDistance )
	set 	maxPos to ( getpos y + doorDistance )
	set doOnce to 1
endif

If ( OnActivate )
	return
endif

; Set a new journal index for all derivative scripts!
If ( GetJournalIndex SW_DantJourn == 30 )
	If ( player->getpos y <= maxPos )
		If ( player->getpos y >= minPos )
			If ( doorRaised == 0 )
				set raiseDoor to 1
			endif
		endif
	endif

	If ( player->getpos y >= maxPos )
		if ( doorRaised )
			set lowerDoor to 1
		endif
	elseif ( player->getpos y <= minPos )
		if ( doorRaised )
			set lowerDoor to 1
		endif
	endif

	if ( raiseDoor )
		If ( doorRaised == 0 )
			setpos z ( basePos + doorDistance )
			set doorRaised to 1
			set raiseDoor to 0
		endif
	Elseif ( lowerDoor )
		if ( doorRaised )
			setpos z basePos
			set doorRaised to 0
			set lowerDoor to 0
		endif
	endif
endif

End tsiAutoDoorJediValley

End tsiAutoDoorScrBase

Begin tsi_JapTreeScript

If ( OnActivate )
	If ( GetJournalIndex "SW_Japor" == 1 )
		player->additem sw_JapSnip 1
		MessageBox "You clip off a piece of the japor tree and stash it in your pouch. You're not sure if you feel comfortable taking another piece of the sacred tree."
		Journal SW_Japor 2
	endif
endif
End tsi_JapTreeScript

Begin tsi_escapechair

If ( OnActivate )
	player->positioncell 1579, -58, 12278, 0, "Tatooine, Sandriver"
Endif

End tsi_escapechair

Begin tsi_forthealthscr

if ( player->getspell tsi_nozerohealth )
	stopscript tsi_forthealthscr
	return
endif

player->addspell tsi_nozerohealth

End tsi_forthealthscr

Begin tsi_koltotanks

short button
short KoltoCost
short QuestionState

if ( OnActivate == 0 )
        if ( QuestionState == 0 )
                Return
        endif
endif

Set KoltoCost to 35

if ( Player->GetItemCount Gold_001 < KoltoCost )
        MessageBox "You do not have enough credits to use this kolto tank." "OK"
        Return
endif

if ( QuestionState == 0 )
        MessageBox "Would you like to make a payment of %.0f and use the kolto tank?" KoltoCost "Yes" "No"
        set QuestionState to 10
endif

;Ask second question 
if ( QuestionState == 10 )

        Set button to GetButtonPressed

        if ( button == 0 )
                MessageBox "What services do you require from this kolto tank?" "Cure Disease" "Cure Poison" "Restore Skeleton and Tissue" "Restore Ability Cognition"
                set QuestionState to 20
        elseif ( button == 1 )
                set QuestionState to 0
        endif

        Return

endif

;perform cure or give message
if ( QuestionState == 20 )

        Set button to GetButtonPressed

        if ( button == 0 )
                if ( Player->GetCommonDisease == 1 )
                        Cast "Cure Common Disease Other" Player
                        Player->RemoveItem Gold_001 35
                        FadeOut,1.0
                        FadeIn,1.0
                else
                        MessageBox "You are not afflicted with a common disease." "OK"
                endif
                Set QuestionState to 0
        endif

;Logic may be re-used later.
;       if ( button == 1 )
;               if ( Player->GetBlightDisease == 1 )
;                       Cast "Cure Blight Disease" Player
;                       Player->RemoveItem Gold_001 35
;                       FadeOut,1.0
;                       FadeIn,1.0
;               else
;                       MessageBox "You are not afflicted with a blight disease." "OK"
;               endif
;               Set QuestionState to 0
;       endif

        if ( button == 1 )
                if ( Player->GetEffect sEffectPoison == 1 )                             ;check for poison effect on player
                        Cast "Cure Poison Touch" Player
                        Player->RemoveItem Gold_001 35
                        FadeOut,1.0
                        FadeIn,1.0
                else
                        MessageBox "You are not poisoned." "OK"
                endif
                Set QuestionState to 0
        endif

        if ( button == 2 )
                Cast "Almsivi Restoration" Player                                       ;restore eight attributes
                Player->RemoveItem Gold_001 35
                FadeOut,1.0
                FadeIn,1.0
                Set QuestionState to 0
        endif

        if ( button == 3 )
                Cast "Almsivi Restore Fighter" Player                                   ;restore eight fighter skills
                Cast "Almsivi Restore Mage" Player                                      ;restore eight mage skills
                Cast "Almsivi Restore Stealth" Player                                   ;restore eight stealth skills
                Cast "Almsivi Restore Other" Player                                     ;restore three other skills
                Player->RemoveItem Gold_001 35
                FadeOut,1.0
                FadeIn,1.0
                Set QuestionState to 0
        endif

endif

end

name: Welcome to Starwind
text:
<FONT COLOR="ECE7AC" SIZE="3" FACE="Magic Cards">
Hello! Thank you for playing Starwind. In this room you'll find nearly a dozen life paths to choose from, only one of which will allow you to play Starwind's original main quest. Choose your path, wanderer.
Hey there. Ready to go back to Nar Shaddaa?
Hey, buddy. Wanna go to vvardenfell?
I'll keep an eye out for your corpse, then.
Smart thinking, traveler. Consider it done.
Well, I like your thinking traveler, but you seem a bit short on credits. Try again when you can afford the job.
Heard you're in a bit of a bind there, stranger. Perhaps you'd like me to take care of that for you?
script_text:
Choice "Yeah, please, I barely made it here." 1
Choice "No thanks, I can handle myself out there." 2

text: Pleasure to meet you, stranger. The name's Jett. I take care of the cartel's legal troubles. I can take care of yours, too... for a price.
A pleasure, stranger. Did we have business to discuss?
What glorious end awaits us?
Let's find a fight worthy of a Mandalorian!
Just waiting on my ransom to cash out and then I'll pick him from the jailhouse and be out of here for a while.

Ah, it seems you have been given access out of Sandriver. I have a business deal for you if you are interested in a little something extra while you're out there. Somewhere in the Dune Sea is a fabled tree, called the Japor Tree. Bring me some snippets of this tree to study for my research, and in return I will make you a quarterstaff from its Ivory. They say the tree has paralyzing effects.
script_text:
Journal "SW_Japor" 1
StopSound "JaporGreet1"
PlaySound3d "JaporGreet2"
StopSound "JaporGreet3"
StopSound "JaporGreet4"
StopSound "Japor1"
StopSound "Japor2"

text: Very well, then. You are now a %NextPCRank of the Republic Fleet, %PCName. I'll update the records here and unlock the door, go find Captain Shell upstairs in the barracks. Oh, and you'd best put on this uniform before you go talk to him.
script_text:
PCRaiseRank
ModDisposition 5
player->additem SW_RepCuirassQuest 1
player->additem SW_ShirtBlack 1
player->additem SW_PantsBlack 1
Journal SW_Republic 5
Set HasJoinedRepublic to 1
StopSound "RepRecGreet"
StopSound "RepRecJoin1"
PlaySound3d "RepRecJoin2"
StopSound "RepRecJoin3"
StopSound "RepRecJoin4"

text: Gear up and head to the barracks, %NextPCRank. Report to Captain Price for your orders. And welcome to the Sith Fleet.
script_text:
PCRaiseRank
ModDisposition 5
Journal SW_Sith 5
player->additem SW_SithCuirassQuest 1
player->additem SW_ShirtBlack 1
player->additem SW_PantsBlack 1
Set HasJoinedSith to 1

text: Uh, well, feel free to enjoy the scenery, I guess.
Let's get out of this trash pile, traveler.
script_text:
Goodbye
player->removeitem gold_001 25000
player->positioncell 4145 5350 12509 0 "Nar Shaddaa, Vvardenfell Hanger"

text: Welp, it looks like you're stuck here then, doesn't it?
Uh, yeah, I mean, it's only twenty five thousand credits to get back. I'll accept whatever passes for the local currency around here.
script_text:
Choice "You're a real ass... Here" 1
Choice "No, I like it here. I think I'll stay for a time." 2

text: Come back when you've came to your senses, then.
Suit up and let's get going, then. It's a long trip.
Sorry, pal. Come back when you're not too broke too afford the trip.
That's right, only a hundred thousand credits a trip.
script_text:
Choice "Sure, I guess I'll pay up." 1
Choice "No way, I don't think I can trust you." 2

text: You've brought me the Ivory? Very well, the quarterstaff was already crafted, but I need raw materials in order to study them. Enjoy your staff, adventurer, I imagine it will come in handy in  your line of work, and thank you. I will put in a good word for you with my fellow colleagues.
script_text:
Journal "SW_Japor" 3
player->removeitem SW_JapSnip 1
player->additem SW_JaporStaff, 1
player->modReputation 1
StopSound "JaporGreet1"
StopSound "JaporGreet2"
StopSound "JaporGreet3"
StopSound "JaporGreet4"
PlaySound3d "Japor1"
StopSound "Japor2"

text: I have received the staff, based on the shape of it I can assume it's made for Echani fighting styles. My reputation with the Czerka Corporation has improved as well.
I have acquired a piece of the Japor tree. I should be careful with this...
